verbose_text: AMFR knockdown resulted in significantly decreased protein levels of detectable ROCK2, Bcl-2 and cyclin D1, compared with the untransfected and scrambled siRNA transfected cells (P < 0.05; XREF_FIG), whereas transfection with AMFR-C resulted in significantly increased protein levels of ROCK2, Bcl-2 and cyclin D1, compared with the cells transfected with the pcDNA3.1 plasmid (P < 0.05; XREF_FIG).
